com.thomsonreuters.upa.codec

Interface MsgKey


  • public interface MsgKey
    UPA Message Key houses a variety of attributes used to help identify the contents flowing within a particular stream. This information, in conjunction with domainType and quality of service information, can be used to uniquely identify a data stream.
    See Also:
    Msg, MsgKeyFlags

      • clear

        void clear()
        Clears MsgKey object. Useful for object reuse during encoding. While decoding, MsgKey object can be reused without using clear().

      • serviceId

        void serviceId(int serviceId)
        The identifier associated with a service (a logical mechanism that provides or enables access to a set of capabilities). This value should correspond to the service content being requested or provided. In UPA, a service corresponds to a subset of content provided by a component, where the Source Directory domain defines specific attributes associated with each service. These attributes include information such as QoS, the specific domain types available, and any dictionaries required to consume information from the service. The Source Directory domain model can obtain this and other types of information. Must be in the range of 0 - 65535.
        Parameters:
        serviceId - the serviceId to set

      • serviceId

        int serviceId()
        The identifier associated with a service (a logical mechanism that provides or enables access to a set of capabilities). This value should correspond to the service content being requested or provided. In UPA, a service corresponds to a subset of content provided by a component, where the Source Directory domain defines specific attributes associated with each service. These attributes include information such as QoS, the specific domain types available, and any dictionaries required to consume information from the service. The Source Directory domain model can obtain this and other types of information.
        Returns:
        the serviceId

      • nameType

        void nameType(int nameType)
        Numeric value, typically enumerated, that indicates the type of the name member. Examples are User Name or RIC (i.e., the Reuters Instrument Code). name types are defined on a per-domain model basis. Must be in the range of 0 - 255.
        Parameters:
        nameType - the nameType to set

      • filter

        void filter(long filter)
        Combination of filterId bit values that describe content for domain model types with a FilterList payload. Filter identifier values are defined by the corresponding domain model specification. Must be in the range of 0 - 4294967296 (2^32).
        • When specified in RequestMsg, filter conveys information about desired entries in responses
        • When specified on a message housing a FilterList payload, filter conveys information about which filter entries are present.
        Parameters:
        filter - the filter to set

      • filter

        long filter()
        Combination of filterId bit values that describe content for domain model types with a FilterList payload. Filter identifier values are defined by the corresponding domain model specification.
        • When specified in RequestMsg, filter conveys information about desired entries in responses
        • When specified on a message housing a FilterList payload, filter conveys information about which filter entries are present.
        Returns:
        the filter

      • identifier

        void identifier(int identifier)
        User specified numeric identifier, is defined on a per-domain model basis. Must be in the range of -2147483648 - 2147483647.
        Parameters:
        identifier - the identifier to set

      • attribContainerType

        void attribContainerType(int attribContainerType)
        Container Type of the msgKey attributes. Must be a container type from the DataTypes enumeration in the range DataTypes.CONTAINER_TYPE_MIN to 255. Can indicate the presence of a UPA container type (value DataTypes.NO_DATA - 224) or some type of customer-defined container type (value 225 - 255).
        Parameters:
        attribContainerType - the attribContainerType to set

      • attribContainerType

        int attribContainerType()
        Container Type of the msgKey attributes. Must be a container type from the DataTypes enumeration. Can indicate the presence of a UPA container type (value DataTypes.NO_DATA - 224) or some type of customer-defined container type (value 225 - 255).
        Returns:
        the attribContainerType

      • encodedAttrib

        Encoded MsgKey attribute information, used for additional identification attributes. Contents are typically specified in the domain model. Type is specified by attribContainerType.
        Parameters:
        encodedAttrib - the encodedAttrib to set

      • encodedAttrib

      • copy

        int copy(MsgKey destKey)
        Performs a deep copy of a MsgKey. Expects all memory to be owned and managed by user. If the memory for the buffers (i.e. name, attrib) are not provided, they will be created.
        Parameters:
        destKey - Destination to copy into. It cannot be null.
        Returns:
        CodecReturnCodes.SUCCESS, if the key is copied successfully, CodecReturnCodes.BUFFER_TOO_SMALL if the buffer provided is too small

      • addFilterId

        int addFilterId(int filterId)
        Adds a FilterId to the key filter.
        Parameters:
        filterId - The FilterId you want added to the filter. (e.g. STATE)
        Returns:
        Failure if this key does not contain filter element, INVALID_DATA if the filterId is greater then maximum filterID value (31), and SUCCESS otherwise
        See Also:
        Directory.ServiceFilterIds
